properties.DESCRIPTION: the tree is big with many leaves. It grows a fruit named Java Apple, or commonly known as 'jambu". It is special as this fruit is commonly seen in markets in Singapore and seeing it growing naturally on a tree is very interesting. We eat the fruits once ripe. At night, multiple bats are seen patrolling around the tree, eating the fruits. In the morning, broken and damaged fruits can be found on the floor, for those were the ones eaten by the local bats.

properties.DESCRIPTION: The Bodhi Tree at Bartley Residences was one of the twelve seeds that were brought by monks from Sri Lanka in the nineteenth century. It has age of approximately 120 years (as at 2007), is over 30 metres tall and has a girth of 8.5 metres which is considered one of the most ancient and largest Bodhi Tree in Singapore according to verifications made by the Nature Society Singapore and National Parks Board separately.
properties.Name: KJ Er

properties.DESCRIPTION: I didn't plant this tree but this tree exists at the entrance of Sunshine Park. There is a bench under it and it's nice and shaaady. If you sit on this bench under the tree, there is a nice view of the park. You can't really see the playground well from your peripheral vision. Oooh i see a doggo in the middle of the park and i think i heard a lizzard. Ok bye! Hope this was interesting!
